Heat oil in 12 inch non stick sauté pan over medium heat until warm. Season Scallops with salt and pepper; add to pan and sauté for 1 minute each side. Add onions and garlic, sauté for 1 minute. Reduce heat to low, add vinegar, sugar and butter, cook for 1-2 minutes or until thickened. Serve over rice pilaf and sautéed spinach. Enjoy!